id: pm-nf7q
title: "Scoped renderer ownership: safe package renderers should not keep isolated package doctor in warning state"
description: Add command or result ownership metadata for extension renderers so doctor can distinguish globally corrupting overrides from safe null-fallback renderers used only by their package commands.
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,diagnostics,extensions,packages,renderers
created_at: "2026-07-15T20:00:19.764Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-15T20:02:16.212Z"
author: codex-audit-20260715
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "The renderer registration contract can declare command paths or a result discriminator without breaking existing callbacks; doctor warns for unscoped or provably unsafe global overrides but treats declared safe ownership as healthy; pm-changelog JSON and TOON marker renderers are migrated to the scoped contract and isolated deep doctor is warning-free; unrelated commands still fall back to native rendering; collisions between packages remain visible; SDK types, define or compose helpers, scaffold, package-author docs, describe output, runtime contracts, and focused real-CLI plus SDK-harness tests are updated together"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: medium
confidence: high
