body: "Live reproduction on current main with only project packages: pm package doctor --project --isolated --detail deep --trace --json returns warning status for pm-changelog renderers json and toon. The package callback is well-behaved and returns null for every non-marker result, so output is not corrupted; however doctor sees only global registration and cannot prove ownership. Closed pm-5teq correctly introduced warnings for dangerous global overrides and must not be reversed. Open pm-ixoa covers an actual calendar and guide-shell service collision. This item adds positive scoping metadata so safe package renderers can be both explicit and warning-free."
